    <h1>Schools of the Republic</h1>
    <p class="kicker">Sullivan and Bird, 2025. Substrate v1.3. ~45,000 words across two parts and fifty state entries.</p>

    <h2>Part I — The Republic Builds</h2>
    <p>Nine essays tracing the school-trust compact from the 1785 Land Ordinance through admission-era doublings, the school clause, fiduciary breach, and recovery. Currently published as the Sacred Compact essay sequence:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/reading/sacred-compact-prologue/">Prologue</a></li>
      <li><a href="/reading/sacred-compact-i-the-question/">I. The Question</a></li>
      <li>(Continue through the eight Sacred Compact essays.)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Part I content is being unified into a continuous narrative in a future revision pass.</p>

    <h2>Part II — Fifty States</h2>
    <p>One encyclopedia entry per state, regrouped by era cohort with admission dates. Each entry covers constitutional architecture, admission-act provisions, permanent fund corpus, federal grant acreage, and current trust-integrity status.</p>
    <p><a href="/reading/">Browse all 50 state entries in the Reading Room →</a></p>

    <hr class="archival-divider">

    <p>This encyclopedia is the substrate for the rest of the library. The <a href="/atlas/">Atlas</a>, the <a href="/counting/">Counting House</a>, and the <a href="/reading/sacred-compact-prologue/">Sacred Compact</a> white paper all draw from these state entries.</p>
